/**

 * Ã°ÅÝÅÅÐò Ê±¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶È O(n^2) ¿Õ¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶ÈO(1)

 */

public class BubbleSort {

 

   public static void bubbleSort(int[] data) {

 

      System.out.println("¿ªÊ¼ÅÅÐò");

      int arrayLength = data.length;

 

      for (int i = 0; i < arrayLength - 1; i++) {

 

         boolean flag = false;

 

         for (int j = 0; j < arrayLength - 1 - i; j++) {

            if(data[j] > data[j + 1]){

               int temp = data[j + 1];

               data[j + 1] = data[j];

               data[j] = temp;

               flag = true;

            }

         }

 

         System.out.println(java.util.Arrays.toString(data));

 

         if (!flag)

            break;

      }

   }

 

   public static void main(String[] args) {

 

      int[] data = { 9, -16, 21, 23, -30, -49, 21, 30, 30 };

 

      System.out.println("ÅÅÐòÖ®Ç°£º\n" + java.util.Arrays.toString(data));

 

      bubbleSort(data);

 

      System.out.println("ÅÅÐòÖ®ºó£º\n" + java.util.Arrays.toString(data));

   }

}

/**

 * ¶þ·Ö²éÕÒ Ê±¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶ÈO(log2n);¿Õ¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶ÈO(1)

 */

 

def binarySearch(arr:Array[Int],left:Int,right:Int,findVal:Int): Int={
  if(left>right){//µÝ¹éÍË³öÌõ¼þ£¬ÕÒ²»µ½£¬·µ»Ø-1
    -1
  }

  val midIndex = (left+right)/2

  if (findVal < arr(midIndex)){//Ïò×óµÝ¹é²éÕÒ
    binarySearch(arr,left,midIndex,findVal)
  }else if(findVal > arr(midIndex)){//ÏòÓÒµÝ¹é²éÕÒ
    binarySearch(arr,midIndex,right,findVal)
  }else{//²éÕÒµ½£¬·µ»ØÏÂ±ê
    midIndex
  }
}

ÍØÕ¹ÐèÇó£ºµ±Ò»¸öÓÐÐòÊý×éÖÐ£¬ÓÐ¶à¸öÏàÍ¬µÄÊýÖµÊ±£¬ÈçºÎ½«ËùÓÐµÄÊýÖµ¶¼²éÕÒµ½¡£

´úÂëÊµÏÖÈçÏÂ£º

/*

  {1,8, 10, 89, 1000, 1000£¬1234} µ±Ò»¸öÓÐÐòÊý×éÖÐ£¬ÓÐ¶à¸öÏàÍ¬µÄÊýÖµÊ±£¬ÈçºÎ½«ËùÓÐµÄÊýÖµ¶¼²éÕÒµ½£¬±ÈÈçÕâÀïµÄ 1000.

  //·ÖÎö

  1. ·µ»ØµÄ½á¹ûÊÇÒ»¸ö¿É±äÊý×é ArrayBuffer

  2. ÔÚÕÒµ½½á¹ûÊ±£¬Ïò×ó±ßÉ¨Ãè£¬ÏòÓÒ±ßÉ¨Ãè [Ìõ¼þ]

  3. ÕÒµ½½á¹ûºó£¬¾Í¼ÓÈëµ½ArrayBuffer

   */

  def binarySearch2(arr: Array[Int], l: Int, r: Int,

                    findVal: Int): ArrayBuffer[Int] = {

 

    //ÕÒ²»µ½Ìõ¼þ?

    if (l > r) {

      return ArrayBuffer()

    }

 

    val midIndex = (l + r) / 2

    val midVal = arr(midIndex)

    if (midVal > findVal) {

      //Ïò×ó½øÐÐµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

      binarySearch2(arr, l, midIndex - 1, findVal)

    } else if (midVal < findVal) { //ÏòÓÒ½øÐÐµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

      binarySearch2(arr, midIndex + 1, r, findVal)

    } else {

      println("midIndex=" + midIndex)

      //¶¨ÒåÒ»¸ö¿É±äÊý×é

      val resArr = ArrayBuffer[Int]()

      //Ïò×ó±ßÉ¨Ãè

      var temp = midIndex - 1

      breakable {

        while (true) {

          if (temp < 0 || arr(temp) != findVal) {

            break()

          }

          if (arr(temp) == findVal) {

            resArr.append(temp)

          }

          temp -= 1

        }

      }

      //½«ÖÐ¼äÕâ¸öË÷Òý¼ÓÈë

      resArr.append(midIndex)

      //ÏòÓÒ±ßÉ¨Ãè

      temp = midIndex + 1

      breakable {

        while (true) {

          if (temp > arr.length - 1 || arr(temp) != findVal) {

            break()

          }

          if (arr(temp) == findVal) {

            resArr.append(temp)

          }

          temp += 1

        }

      }

      return resArr

    }

/**

 * ¿ìÅÅ 

 * Ê±¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶È:Æ½¾ùÊ±¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶ÈÎªO(nlogn)

 * ¿Õ¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶È:O(logn)£¬ÒòÎªµÝ¹éÕ»¿Õ¼äµÄÊ¹ÓÃÎÊÌâ

 */

def quickSort(list: List[Int]): List[Int] = list match {

    case Nil => Nil

    case List() => List()

    case head :: tail =>

      val (left, right) = tail.partition(_ < head)

      quickSort(left) ::: head :: quickSort(right)

  }

/**

 * ¿ìÅÅ 

 * Ê±¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶È:O(nlogn)

 * ¿Õ¼ä¸´ÔÓ¶È:O(n)

 */

def merge(left: List[Int], right: List[Int]): List[Int] = (left, right) match {

    case (Nil, _) => right

    case (_, Nil) => left

    case (x :: xTail, y :: yTail) =>

      if (x <= y) x :: merge(xTail, right)

      else y :: merge(left, yTail)

  }

class TreeNode(treeNo:Int){

  val no = treeNo

  var left:TreeNode = null

  var right:TreeNode = null

 

  //ºóÐò±éÀú

  def postOrder():Unit={

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹éÊä³ö×ó×ÓÊ÷

    if(this.left != null){

      this.left.postOrder

    }

    //ÏòÓÒµÝ¹éÊä³öÓÒ×ÓÊ÷

    if (this.right != null) {

      this.right.postOrder

    }

 

    //Êä³öµ±Ç°½ÚµãÖµ

    printf("½ÚµãÐÅÏ¢ no=%d \n",no)

  }

 

  //ÖÐÐò±éÀú

  def infixOrder():Unit={

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹éÊä³ö×ó×ÓÊ÷

    if(this.left != null){

      this.left.infixOrder()

    }

 

    //Êä³öµ±Ç°½ÚµãÖµ

    printf("½ÚµãÐÅÏ¢ no=%d \n",no)

 

    //ÏòÓÒµÝ¹éÊä³öÓÒ×ÓÊ÷

    if (this.right != null) {

      this.right.infixOrder()

    }

  }

 

  //Ç°Ðò±éÀú

  def preOrder():Unit={

    //Êä³öµ±Ç°½ÚµãÖµ

    printf("½ÚµãÐÅÏ¢ no=%d \n",no)

 

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹éÊä³ö×ó×ÓÊ÷

    if(this.left != null){

      this.left.postOrder()

    }

 

    //ÏòÓÒµÝ¹éÊä³öÓÒ×ÓÊ÷

    if (this.right != null) {

      this.right.preOrder()

    }

  }

 

  //ºóÐò±éÀú²éÕÒ

  def postOrderSearch(no:Int): TreeNode = {

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹éÊä³ö×ó×ÓÊ÷

    var resNode:TreeNode = null

    if (this.left != null) {

      resNode = this.left.postOrderSearch(no)

    }

    if (resNode != null) {

      return resNode

    }

    if (this.right != null) {

      resNode = this.right.postOrderSearch(no)

    }

    if (resNode != null) {

      return resNode

    }

    println("ttt~~")

    if (this.no == no) {

      return this

    }

    resNode

  }

 

  //ÖÐÐò±éÀú²éÕÒ

  def infixOrderSearch(no:Int): TreeNode = {

 

 

    var resNode : TreeNode = null

    //ÏÈÏò×óµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

    if (this.left != null) {

      resNode = this.left.infixOrderSearch(no)

    }

    if (resNode != null) {

      return resNode

    }

    println("yyy~~")

    if (no == this.no) {

      return this

    }

    //ÏòÓÒµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

    if (this.right != null) {

      resNode = this.right.infixOrderSearch(no)

    }

    return resNode

 

  }

 

  //Ç°Ðò²éÕÒ

  def preOrderSearch(no:Int): TreeNode = {

    if (no == this.no) {

      return this

    }

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

    var resNode : TreeNode = null

    if (this.left != null) {

      resNode = this.left.preOrderSearch(no)

    }

    if (resNode != null){

      return  resNode

    }

    //ÏòÓÒ±ßµÝ¹é²éÕÒ

    if (this.right != null) {

      resNode = this.right.preOrderSearch(no)

    }

 

    return resNode

  }

 

  //É¾³ý½Úµã

  //É¾³ý½Úµã¹æÔò

  //1Èç¹ûÉ¾³ýµÄ½ÚµãÊÇÒ¶×Ó½Úµã£¬ÔòÉ¾³ý¸Ã½Úµã

  //2Èç¹ûÉ¾³ýµÄ½ÚµãÊÇ·ÇÒ¶×Ó½Úµã£¬ÔòÉ¾³ý¸Ã×ÓÊ÷

 

  def delNode(no:Int): Unit = {

    //Ê×ÏÈ±È½Ïµ±Ç°½ÚµãµÄ×ó×Ó½ÚµãÊÇ·ñÎªÒªÉ¾³ýµÄ½Úµã

    if (this.left != null && this.left.no == no) {

      this.left = null

      return

    }

    //±È½Ïµ±Ç°½ÚµãµÄÓÒ×Ó½ÚµãÊÇ·ñÎªÒªÉ¾³ýµÄ½Úµã

    if (this.right != null && this.right.no == no) {

      this.right = null

      return

    }

    //Ïò×óµÝ¹éÉ¾³ý

    if (this.left != null) {

      this.left.delNode(no)

    }

    //ÏòÓÒµÝ¹éÉ¾³ý

    if (this.right != null) {

      this.right.delNode(no)

    }

  }

}

class BinaryTree{

  var root:TreeNode = null

 

  //ºóÐò±éÀú

  def postOrder(): Unit = {

    if (root != null){

      root.postOrder()

    }else {

      println("µ±Ç°¶þ²æÊ÷Îª¿Õ£¬²»ÄÜ±éÀú")

}

}

    //ÖÐÐò±éÀú

    def infixOrder(): Unit = {

      if (root != null){

        root.infixOrder()

      }else {

        println("µ±Ç°¶þ²æÊ÷Îª¿Õ£¬²»ÄÜ±éÀú")

      }

    }

    //Ç°Ðò±éÀú

    def preOrder(): Unit = {

      if (root != null){

        root.preOrder()

      }else {

        println("µ±Ç°¶þ²æÊ÷Îª¿Õ£¬²»ÄÜ±éÀú")

      }

    }

 

    //ºóÐò±éÀú²éÕÒ

    def postOrderSearch(no:Int): TreeNode = {

      if (root != null) {

        root.postOrderSearch(no)

      }else{

        null

      }

    }

 

    //ÖÐÐò±éÀú²éÕÒ

    def infixOrderSeacher(no:Int): TreeNode = {

      if (root != null) {

        return root.infixOrderSearch(no)

      }else {

        return null

      }

    }

 

    //Ç°Ðò²éÕÒ

    def preOrderSearch(no:Int): TreeNode = {

 

      if (root != null) {

        return root.preOrderSearch(no)

      }else{

        //println("µ±Ç°¶þ²æÊ÷Îª¿Õ£¬²»ÄÜ²éÕÒ")

        return null

      }

    }

//É¾³ý½Úµã

    def delNode(no:Int): Unit = {

      if (root != null) {

        //ÏÈ´¦ÀíÒ»ÏÂrootÊÇ²»ÊÇÒªÉ¾³ýµÄ

        if (root.no == no){

          root = null

        }else {

          root.delNode(no)

        }

      }

    

  }

4.8.2 SqoopÊý¾Ýµ¼³öÒ»ÖÂÐÔÎÊÌâ

1£©³¡¾°1£ºÈçSqoopÔÚµ¼³öµ½MysqlÊ±£¬Ê¹ÓÃ4¸öMapÈÎÎñ£¬¹ý³ÌÖÐÓÐ2¸öÈÎÎñÊ§°Ü£¬ÄÇ´ËÊ±MySQLÖÐ´æ´¢ÁËÁíÍâÁ½¸öMapÈÎÎñµ¼ÈëµÄÊý¾Ý£¬´ËÊ±ÀÏ°åÕýºÃ¿´µ½ÁËÕâ¸ö±¨±íÊý¾Ý¡£¶ø¿ª·¢¹¤³ÌÊ¦·¢ÏÖÈÎÎñÊ§°Üºó£¬»áµ÷ÊÔÎÊÌâ²¢×îÖÕ½«È«²¿Êý¾ÝÕýÈ·µÄµ¼ÈëMySQL£¬ÄÇºóÃæÀÏ°åÔÙ´Î¿´±¨±íÊý¾Ý£¬·¢ÏÖ±¾´Î¿´µ½µÄÊý¾ÝÓëÖ®Ç°µÄ²»Ò»ÖÂ£¬ÕâÔÚÉú²ú»·¾³ÊÇ²»ÔÊÐíµÄ¡£

¹ÙÍø£ºhttp://sqoop.apache.org/docs/1.4.6/SqoopUserGuide.html

Since Sqoop breaks down export process into multiple transactions, it is possible that a failed export job may result in partial data being committed to the database. This can further lead to subsequent jobs failing due to insert collisions in some cases, or lead to duplicated data in others. You can overcome this problem by specifying a staging table via the --staging-table option which acts as an auxiliary table that is used to stage exported data. The staged data is finally moved to the destination table in a single transaction.

–staging-table·½Ê½

sqoop export --connect jdbc:mysql://192.168.137.10:3306/user_behavior --username root --password 123456 --table app_cource_study_report --columns watch_video_cnt,complete_video_cnt,dt --fields-terminated-by "\t" --export-dir "/user/hive/warehouse/tmp.db/app_cource_study_analysis_${day}" --staging-table app_cource_study_report_tmp --clear-staging-table --input-null-string '\N'

2£©³¡¾°2£ºÉèÖÃmapÊýÁ¿Îª1¸ö£¨²»ÍÆ¼ö£¬ÃæÊÔ¹ÙÏëÒªµÄ´ð°¸²»Ö»Õâ¸ö£©

¶à¸öMapÈÎÎñÊ±£¬²ÉÓÃ–staging-table·½Ê½£¬ÈÔÈ»¿ÉÒÔ½â¾öÊý¾ÝÒ»ÖÂÐÔÎÊÌâ¡£

(1) select date, sum(case when result = "win" then 1 else 0 end) as "win", sum(case when result = "lose" then 1 else 0 end) as "lose" from info group by date;

(2) select a.date, a.result as win, b.result as lose

¡¡¡¡from

¡¡¡¡(select date, count(result) as result from info where result = "win" group by date) as a

¡¡¡¡join

¡¡¡¡(select date, count(result) as result from info where result = "lose" group by date) as b

on a.date = b.date;
